        "filename": "util/BUILD.gn",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 466,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-24T16:23:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, Crashpad hasn\u0027t needed to interact via FIDL yet, so there\u0027s not currently any build infrastructure for bindings generation. That will need to be resolved for standalone/dart/external. Could they be pre-generated in the SDK distribution for C perhaps?\n\nChromium has a bunch of stuff to build the bindings for languages it needs, e.g. https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/fuchsia-sdk/gen_build_defs.py and https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/fuchsia-sdk/fuchsia_sdk_pkg.gni will I believe cause this one to be generated.",
      "parentUuid": "cd7e819d_d474d5da",
      "revId": "55b5ce0b75677bcf35e8af79a3925842a873f801",
